<p>Use stroke width utilities to control the thickness of text
outlines.</p>
<h3 id="doc-syntax">Syntax</h3>
<pre class="html"><code>.stroke-width-[value]</code></pre>
<p>Where <code>[value]</code> can be a spacing-based scale or fixed
pixel value.</p>
<pre class="html"><code>.stroke-[color-name]</code></pre>
<p>Where <code>[color-name]</code> refers to any available color defined
in your design system (e.g., <code>red</code>, <code>blue-500</code>,
<code>black-950</code>, etc.).</p>
<h3 id="doc-examples">Examples</h3>
<div class="bold fs-3xl color-grey stroke-red stroke-width-1 mt-4">
Red strokes
</div>
<pre class="html"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;bold fs-3xl color-grey stroke-red stroke-width-1&quot;&gt;Red strokes&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
<div class="bold fs-6xl color-grey stroke-blue stroke-width-3 mt-3">
Big strokes
</div>
<pre class="html"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;bold fs-6xl color-grey stroke-blue stroke-width-3&quot;&gt;Big strokes&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
